RingEquiv.symm\">symm</a></span>\n    <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#algebraMap\">algebraMap</a> (<span class=\"fn\">Rₚ</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Quotient.html#HasQuotient.Quotient\">⧸</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/LocalRing/MaximalIdeal/Defs.html#IsLocalRing.maximalIdeal\">IsLocalRing.maximalIdeal</a> <span class=\"fn\">Rₚ</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\">Sₚ</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Quotient.html#HasQuotient.Quotient\">⧸</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#Ideal.map\">Ideal.map</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#algebraMap\">algebraMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span> <span class=\"fn\">Sₚ</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span>))</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The following diagram where the vertical maps are the algebra maps and the horizontal maps are\n`Localization.AtPrime.equivQuotMaximalIdeal.symm` and\n`Localization.AtPrime.equivQuotientMapOfIsMaximal.symm` commutes:\n```\nRₚ ⧸ 𝓂 ──▶ R ⧸ p\n  │         │\nSₚ ⧸ 𝒫 ──▶ S ⧸ P\n```\nHere, `𝓂` denotes the maximal ideal of `Rₚ` and `𝒫` the image of `P` in `Sₚ`.\nNote that result is stated in that direction since this is the formulation needed for the proof\nof `Localization.AtPrime.inertiaDeg_map_eq_inertiaDeg`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/AtPrime/Extension.html#IsLocalization.AtPrime.algebraMap_equivQuotMaximalIdeal_symm_apply","kind":"theorem","line":138,"name":"IsLocalization.AtPrime.algebraMap_equivQuotMaximalIdeal_symm_apply","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/AtPrime/Extension.lean#L138-L159"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/