 class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Q</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maximal.html#Ideal.IsMaximal\">IsMaximal</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IntegralClosure/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra.IsIntegral\">Algebra.IsIntegral</a> <span class=\"fn\">Rₚ</span> <span class=\"fn\">Sₚ</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">Q</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/LocalRing/MaximalIdeal/Defs.html#IsLocalRing.maximalIdeal\">IsLocalRing.maximalIdeal</a> <span class=\"fn\">Rₚ</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Over.html#Ideal.primesOver\">primesOver</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">Sₚ</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The nonzero prime ideals of `Sₚ` are prime ideals over the maximal ideal of `Rₚ`.\nSee `Localization.AtPrime.primesOverEquivPrimesOver` for the bijection between the prime ideals\nof `Sₚ` over the maximal ideal of `Rₚ` and the primes ideals of `S` above `p`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/AtPrime/Extension.html#IsLocalization.AtPrime.mem_primesOver_of_isPrime","kind":"theorem","line":51,"name":"IsLocalization.AtPrime.mem_primesOver_of_isPrime","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/AtPrime/Extension.lean#L51-L60"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.NumberTheory.RamificationInertia.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.AtPrime.Extension"}